          and the land. This tourist spot, often visited by tourists after
          touring the island, is perfect for family vacations.
        </p>
        <h3 class="text-h3">Attractions of Tanjung Kelayang Beach:</h3>
        <p class="text-home">
          Tanjung Kelayang Beach is a peninsula that juts out to the north. Its
          coastline stretches for 4 kilometers to Tanjung Tinggi Beach on the
          east side. The beach is spacious with fine sand, making it suitable
          for strolling or simply lying down to enjoy the gentle breeze. The sea
          water has a gradation of clear green near the shallow shoreline,
          gradually turning into dark blue. The waves are not too high, making
          it popular for swimming.
        </p>

        <p class="text-home">
          Another unique feature of Tanjung Kelayang Beach is that it appears
          wider when the tide recedes in the morning. The beach has a
          significant tidal range, with the water receding far from the shore.
          Like other beaches in Belitung, Tanjung Kelayang Beach is adorned with
          granite rocks at the tip of the cape. Brave visitors can climb these
          rocks to admire the panoramic view of Tanjung Kelayang. One of the
          famous rocks resembles the head of a bird, and it is said to be the
          origin of the name "Tanjung Kelayang." This uniqueness makes the
          granite rocks a favorite spot for photography. The name "Kelayang"
          refers to the local swiftlet bird commonly found around the beach.
        </p>

        <h4 class="text-h3">Directions to Tanjung Kelayang Beach:</h4>
        <ul>
