            Tanjung Kelayang Beach is approximately 27.5 kilometers from Tanjung
            Pandan, the capital of Belitung Regency, with a travel time of about
            37 minutes. The journey can be made via Air Saga Road and Tanjung
            Pandan-Tanjung Kelayang Road.
          </p>
          <li><h5 class="text-h5">By Air:</h5></li>
          <p class="text-home">
            Visitors from outside the city can fly to HAS Hanandjoeddin Airport
            in Tanjung Pandan. If having difficulty finding public
            transportation from the airport, visitors can rent a car or use
            travel services to explore Belitung Island.
          </p>
          <p class="text-home">
            Tanjung Kelayang Beach, with its breathtaking beauty and unique
            features, is indeed a must-visit destination for travelers exploring
            the wonders of Belitung.
          </p>
          <li><h5 class="text-h5">By Sea Travel:</h5></li>
          <p class="text-home">
            Another alternative transportation route is through sea travel,
            especially for visitors coming from Lampung City and around Jambi.
            The journey will pass through Boom Baru Port in Palembang City. From
            Pangkal Pinang, visitors can take a ferry from Balam Port to Tanjung
            Pandan Port in Belitung. Visitors from Jakarta can travel via
            Tanjung Priok Port to Tanjung Pandan.
          </p>
